 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "Create task: LIVESTORE-2: Write-through write_tx — the core mutation that makes the cache always fresh. CONTEXT: Current write_tx() in layout.rs writes an EDN txn file then DELETES store.bin (invalidate_cache). The next load_store() must rebuild from 7K+ EDN files (2.5s). LiveStore replaces this with write-through: write txn file + apply to in-memory store + serialize updated store to store.bin. APPROACH: (1) Add LiveStore::write_tx(&mut self, tx: &TxFile) -> Result<TxFilePath>. Steps: (a) Call layout.write_tx_no_invalidate(tx) — a new DiskLayout method that writes the EDN file and fsyncs but does NOT call invalidate_cache(). (b) Build a Transaction from tx.datoms, commit against self.store, then self.store.transact(committed). This updates MaterializedViews, all 6 indexes, schema, and frontier in-memory. (c) Call self.layout.write_index_cache(&self.store) to serialize the updated store to store.bin. (d) Return the TxFilePath. (2) Add DiskLayout::write_tx_no_invalidate(&self, tx: &TxFile) -> Result<TxFilePath>: same as current write_tx() but without the invalidate_cache() call. The existing write_tx() becomes: write_tx_no_invalidate + invalidate_cache (backward compat for non-LiveStore callers during migration). (3) Error handling: if transact() fails (schema violation), still write the EDN file (durability) but do NOT update store.bin (consistency). Log the error. The next load_store() from another process will attempt the transaction and either succeed or report the same error. (4) If write_index_cache() fails (disk full, permissions), the in-memory store is still updated — the process continues correctly, and the next process will do a one-time rebuild. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After LiveStore::write_tx(), the in-memory store contains the new datoms. (B) store.bin on disk contains the new datoms (deserialize and verify). (C) No call to invalidate_cache() in the LiveStore path. (D) Crash between transact() and write_index_cache() recovers correctly via incremental load on next open. (E) UAQ-6 presentation count tracking in status.rs no longer causes 2.5s penalty. DEPENDS-ON: LIVESTORE-1. FILE: crates/braid/src/live_store.rs + crates/braid/src/layout.rs (write_tx_no_invalidate)"
